<paragraph id="8BAC36BF3624643D9083F819FDB4F7F9" blockId="0.[136,1451,2027,2086]" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis id="B967EAAD3624643D9083F819FEADF7DE" bold="true" box="[136,259,2027,2049]" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Location:—</emphasis>
The true position in Catamarca is sited 
<quantity id="4CEB9B5A3624643D929BF81EFD72F7DD" box="[656,732,2028,2050]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" unit="km" value="600.0">600 km</quantity>
to the north and slightly east of the speculative version provided in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation id="EF824B4E3624643D9139F7E2FDA1F7F9" author="Watson, J. M. &amp; Flores, A. R." box="[306,527,2064,2086]" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" pagination="19 - 23" refId="ref3487" refString="Watson, J. M. &amp; Flores, A. R. (2009) A new and rare rosulate species of Viola (Violaceae) from Argentina. Phytotaxa 2: 19 - 23. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 2.1.3" type="journal article" year="2009">
Watson &amp; 
<collectingCountry id="F304762F3624643D9192F7E2FE7BF7F9" box="[409,469,2064,2086]" name="Indonesia" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Flores</collectingCountry>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAC36BF3625643C90CAFF6CFD5AFE97" blockId="1.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="178">
Information on the water resources of 
<collectingRegion id="49D7F85D3625643C9265FF6CFD47FF67" box="[622,745,158,184]" country="Argentina" name="Catamarca" pageId="1" pageNumber="178">Catamarca</collectingRegion>
, published by the province’s local government (
<bibRefCitation id="EF824B4E3625643C950AFF6CFA31FF67" author="ETISIG &amp; Equipo de Trabajo Interinstitutional &amp; Sistemas de Informacion Geograficas" box="[1281,1439,158,184]" pageId="1" pageNumber="178" pagination="14 - 15" refId="ref2847" refString="ETISIG (Equipo de Trabajo Interinstitutional en Sistemas de Informacion Geograficas) (2014) Cuencas Hidrograficas de la Provincia de Catamarca. Atlas de Catamarca.: 14 - 15. www. atlas. catamarca. gov. ar / PDF / ... / hodrpgragia / cuencas _ catamarca. pdf. (Accessed 17 April 2014)" type="book chapter" year="2014">
<collectionCode id="ED02AE7A3625643C950AFF6CFAF5FF67" box="[1281,1371,158,184]" pageId="1" pageNumber="178">ETISIG</collectionCode>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), positions the Río de Los Nacimientos (otherwise known as Río Las Cuevas) north of Belén, above and to the north of Los Nacimientos village. The valley of the Río Villa Vil lies to the west, and both watercourses meet south of Hualfín to 
<taxonomicName id="4C134D3C3625643C90AFFEF8FE75FEFB" authority="Rio Belen. Several" authorityName="Rio Belen. Several" box="[164,475,266,292]" form="the" pageId="1" pageNumber="178" rank="form">form the Río Belén. Several</taxonomicName>
maps we have consulted confirm this geography. We estimate the probable elevation of the viola site at between 3500 and 
<quantity id="4CEB9B5A3625643C9207FEDCFDCAFE96" box="[524,612,302,329]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="178" unit="m" value="4500.0">4500 m</quantity>
. 
<figureCitation id="13282A3A3625643C9264FEDCFD15FE97" box="[623,699,302,328]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1658,1680]" captionTargetBox="[448,1139,353,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[448,1139,353,1634]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Map of the Southern Cone of SouthAmerica, outlining the Argentinian provinces. Catamarca is dark-shaded, and the location of Viola singlaris denoted as an asterisk. The false, previous location in Mendoza Province, as given for the protologue, is marked with a cross." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5144721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5144721/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="178">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="13282A3A3625643C92D4FEDCFD5EFE97" box="[735,752,302,328]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[317,1271,641,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[317,1271,641,1922]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Physical map of the sector in Catamarca Province, Argentina, where Viola singularis is located. Three outlying towns are identified for orientation. A hatched oblong indicates the Río de Los Nacimientos (or Río Las Cuevas) where the viola was discovered. It is situated above the settlement of Los Nacimientos, shown as a white asterisk within a black circle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5144723" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5144723/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="178">2</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
